erimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/serial\"><code>serial</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/serviceWorker\"><code>serviceWorker</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/storage\"><code>storage</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/userAgent\"><code>userAgent</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/userAgentData\"><code>userAgentData</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/vendor\"><code>vendor</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/vendorSub\"><code>vendorSub</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/webdriver\"><code>webdriver</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/windowControlsOverlay\"><code>windowControlsOverlay</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/xr\"><code>xr</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/canShare\"><code>canShare()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/clearAppBadge\"><code>clearAppBadge()</code></a></li><li><em><code>getBattery()</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getGamepads\"><code>getGamepads()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getUserMedia\"><code>getUserMedia()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-nonstandard\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-nonstandard\"></use>\n</svg><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getVRDisplays\"><code>getVRDisplays()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/javaEnabled\"><code>javaEnabled()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-nonstandard\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-nonstandard\"></use>\n</svg><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/mozIsLocallyAvailable\"><code>mozIsLocallyAvailable()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-nonstandard\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-nonstandard\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/msLaunchUri\"><code>msLaunchUri()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/registerProtocolHandler\"><code>registerProtocolHandler()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/requestMediaKeySystemAccess\"><code>requestMediaKeySystemAccess()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/requestMIDIAccess\"><code>requestMIDIAccess()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/sendBeacon\"><code>sendBeacon()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/setAppBadge\"><code>setAppBadge()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/share\"><code>share()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/taintEnabled\"><code>taintEnabled()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/vibrate\"><code>vibrate()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Battery API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager\"><code>BatteryManager</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getBattery\"><code>Navigator.getBattery()</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong><code>getBattery()</code></strong> method provides information about the\n  system's battery. It returns a battery promise, which is resolved in a\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager\"><code>BatteryManager</code></a> object providing also some new events you can handle to\n  monitor the battery status. This implements the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API\">Battery Status API</a>; see that\n  documentation for additional details, a guide to using the API, and sample code.\n</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> In some browsers access to this feature is controlled by the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Feature-Policy\"><code>Feature-Policy</code></a> directive <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Feature-Policy/battery\"><code>battery</code></a>.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">getBattery()\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<p>None.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> which, when resolved, calls its fulfillment handler with a\n  single parameter: a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager\"><code>BatteryManager</code></a> object which you can use to get\n  information about the battery's state.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"exceptions","title":"Exceptions","isH3":true,"content":"<p>This method doesn't throw true exceptions; instead, it rejects the returned promise, passing into it a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a> whose <code>name</code> is one of the following:</p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"securityerror\"><code>SecurityError</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The User Agent does not expose battery information to insecure contexts and this method was called from insecure context.</p>\n    <div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n      <p><strong>Note:</strong> Old versions of some User Agents might allow use of this feature in insecure contexts.</p>\n    </div>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"notallowederror\"><code>NotAllowedError</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>No User Agent currently throws this exception, but the specification describes the following behaviors:</p>\n    <blockquote>\n      <p>\n        This document is not allowed to use this feature.\n        For example, it might not be explicitly allowed or restricted via <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Feature-Policy\"><code>Feature-Policy</code></a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Feature-Policy/battery\"><code>battery</code></a> feature.\n      </p>\n    </blockquote>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  This example fetches the current charging state of the battery and establishes a\n  handler for the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager/chargingchange_event\" title=\"chargingchange\"><code>chargingchange</code></a> event, so that the charging state is\n  recorded whenever it changes.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> batteryIsCharging <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nnavigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getBattery</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">battery</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  batteryIsCharging <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>charging<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'chargingchange'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    batteryIsCharging <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>charging<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>For more examples and details, see <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API\">Battery Status API</a>.</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/battery/#dom-navigator-getbattery","title":"Battery Status API"}],"query":"api.Navigator.getBattery"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.Navigator.getBattery","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getBattery/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API\">Battery Status API</a></li>\n  <li>\n    <code>Feature-Policy</code> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Feature-Policy/battery\"><code>battery</code></a>\n    feature\n  </li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The getBattery() method provides information about the\n  system's battery. It returns a battery promise, which is resolved in a\n  BatteryManager object providing also some new events you can handle to\n  monitor the battery status. This implements the Battery Status API; see that\n  documentation for additional details, a guide to using the API, and sample code.","popularity":0.001,"modified":"2022-09-13T05:54:54.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Navigator.getBattery()","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"window.navigator.battery","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Navigator.getBattery()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"window.navigator.battery","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Navigator.battery","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Navigator.battery","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Navigator.getBattery()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/navigator/getbattery","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/navigator/getbattery/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/b7556b71e1fc3e89057671b372871e9f33d3f0b8","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator","title":"Navigator"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getBattery","title":"Navigator.getBattery()"}],"pageTitle":"Navigator.getBattery() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}